  "output": "Verified against live code (v1.1-dev), not stale notes. Full audit:\n\n## N+1 query patterns\n\n**1. `ItemInvoiceService.post`** — `ItemInvoiceService.swift:93-99` loops `inventoryRepo.findItemById(input.itemId)` per line. `InventoryRepository` has no batch lookup at all.\n```swift\npublic func findItemsByIds(_ ids: Set<InventoryItem.ID>) throws -> [InventoryItem.ID: InventoryItem] {\n    guard !ids.isEmpty else { return [:] }\n    let placeholders = Array(repeating: \"?\", count: ids.count).joined(separator: \",\")\n    var out: [InventoryItem.ID: InventoryItem] = [:]\n    _ = try db.query(\"SELECT \\(Self.itemColumns) FROM avelo_inventory_items WHERE id IN (\\(placeholders))\",\n                      bind: ids.map { .text($0.uuidString) }) { out[...] = try Self.rowToItem($0) }\n    return out\n}\n```\n\n**2. `AccountTreeCache.reload()`** — `AccountTreeCache.swift:58-67` calls `signedOpeningBalance` per ledger. Root cause: `ReportRepository.swift:249-273` falls back to a single-account `movementTotals` call per ledger, even though `movementTotals(for accountIds:)` is already batch-shaped. Fix: split ledgers into carried-forward vs fallback, batch-call once.\n\n**3. `VoucherService.loadAccounts`** — `VoucherService.swift:1164-1175` loops `accountRepo.findById(id)` on every post. `AccountRepository` has `findByCodes` batch but no `findByIds`. Add one.\n\n**4. `VoucherService.markAccountsUsed`** — `VoucherService.swift:1079-1084` loops `accountRepo.markUsed(id)` despite `markUsedBatch` already existing and being used correctly in `postBatch` (line 192). Called from 6 sites (284, 397, 510, 576, 702, 772). One-line fix: `try accountRepo.markUsedBatch(seen)`.\n\n**5. `BOMService.validateBOMInput`** — `BOMService.swift:75-87`, same missing-batch-method root cause as #1.\n\n## Unnecessary SwiftUI re-renders\n\n**1. `AccountPicker`** — `AccountPicker.swift:147-170`, `sortedAccounts`/`filteredAccounts` are plain computed properties, resort/refilter the whole account list on every render, every keystroke. Cache in `@State`, recompute only `.onChange(of: accounts.map(\\.id))`.\n\n**2. `AccountsView.orderedGroups`** — `AccountsView.swift:142-154` rebuilds the full group hierarchy tree on every body eval, not just when `vm.groups` changes. Move construction into the view model, recompute only inside `reload()`.\n\n**3. GSTView staleness (not what notes claimed)** — `GSTView.swift:28-38` date-range reload is actually fine. Real bug: `.task(id: reloadKey)` guard only rebuilds on `companyId` change, so a same-company `dataRevision` bump (e.g. after posting a voucher) doesn't refresh the GST summary — silently stale. `AccountsView.swift:33-43` has the identical bug shape.\n\n## Caching opportunities\n\n**1. `ReportService`** — only 4 of 10 report methods (`ledger`, `trialBalance`, `profitAndLoss`, `balanceSheet`) go through `ReportCache`. `gstSummary`, `dayBook`, `outstanding`, `stockValuation`, `cashFlow`, `stockAgeing` hit the repo raw every call. Extend existing cache machinery to the rest.\n\n**2. `ReportService.invalidateCache`** — called from 8 sites in `VoucherService`, but `ReportCache.value(for:)` already re-derives `changeToken` and drops stale entries lazily on read. The explicit eager wipe is dead work on every voucher mutation, not a correctness fix.\n\n**3. `GSTViewModel.reload()`** — `GSTView.swift:188-192` calls `svc.summary(...)` then `svc.buildReturn(...)`, but `buildReturn` internally calls `summary()` again — same aggregate JOIN query runs twice. Add a `buildReturn(from summary:)` overload.\n\n## Memory leaks\n\nChecked all 18 `Task {}` sites. **Clean** — every site touching `self` uses `[weak self]` (`AppEnvironment.swift:253-256`, `299-305`; `KeyboardBridge.swift:32-36`). The two without it (`SearchBar.swift`, `VoucherEditViewModel.swift`) never capture `self`, so no cycle exists. Prior \"17 unsafe Task closures\" note was overstated — no fix needed here.\n\n## Redundant computations\n\n**1. `InventoryService.recordMovement`** — `InventoryService.swift:161-224` replays the FIFO/weighted-average valuation **three separate times** per stock movement insert (`runningBalance` → `authoritativeMovementForInsertion` → `republishAuthoritativeValuation`), each re-reading movement history independently. Fix: single replay pass, derive quantity/value/republish set from it.\n\n**2. `LedgerLineRepository.insertBatch` / `VoucherItemLineRepository.insertBatch`** — both loop single-row `INSERT`s per line despite the name. SQLite supports multi-row `VALUES (...),(...)`. Every N-line voucher = N round trips.\n\n**3. `BOMRepository.replaceComponents`** — `BOMRepository.swift:33-52`, same delete-then-loop-insert pattern.\n\nskipped: applying any of these fixes — this was audit-only. say the word on which ones to land first (my pick: #4/markAccountsUsed and #3/GST double-query, both one-liners with real payoff).\n",
